OL,5,Cpatient
OL,7,FPaterson said "no breast surgeon aims
OL,8,Fto leave breast tissue after breast
OL,9,Fsurgery, that's just crazy" but has
OL,10,Fsaid that in individual patients it
OL,11,Fwas sometimes possible to leave
OL,12,F"subcutaneous tissue (fat)".
OL,14,FPaterson carried out needless
OL,15,Foperations over a 14-year period.
OL,17,FWhile working as a breast surgeon
OL,18,Fconsultant, he was diagnosing cancer
OL,19,Fwhen there wasn't any and cutting
OL,20,Fpatients open for no reason.
